Thanks. Ok, then I think I got things right.

And yes, your interpretation is correct (although I cannot tell without the results from anova() if that difference in slopes is really significant).

I am not a big fan of standardizing predictors. Instead, you could rescale M, e.g., divide M by 10 or 100, so one unit then means 10ms or 100ms. Then the slopes won't be quite so small (which is actually the same thing as just multiplying the slopes by the same factor).

